1
00:00:04,738 --> 00:00:08,641
This appears to be a photo of them
smoking inside a karaoke box.

2
00:00:08,708 --> 00:00:11,111
They all admitted to smoking.

3
00:00:11,177 --> 00:00:16,249
The six on the expulsion list
showed no remorse.

4
00:00:16,316 --> 00:00:20,320
The five not listed did show remorse.

5
00:00:20,387 --> 00:00:25,091
This way, only the students on the list
will be expelled.

6
00:00:25,158 --> 00:00:27,093
I want you to expose Moriguchi's plot

7
00:00:27,160 --> 00:00:29,029
to the PTA board tomorrow.

8
00:00:29,095 --> 00:00:32,899
Anyway, I have no motivation for this job!

9
00:00:32,966 --> 00:00:34,434
Just once!

10
00:00:34,501 --> 00:00:36,603
Try confronting it, with all your heart.

11
00:00:38,204 --> 00:00:40,140
To rebuild the school's reputation,

12
00:00:40,206 --> 00:00:42,842
they want to expel students
from "problematic" families.

13
00:00:43,743 --> 00:00:46,012
We already know.

14
00:00:46,679 --> 00:00:48,782
All on the PTA board

15
00:00:49,749 --> 00:00:51,851
support the school's plan.

16
00:00:52,552 --> 00:00:53,720
Why?

17
00:00:54,921 --> 00:00:58,191
I'm glad we have your approval,
President Kobayakawa.

18
00:00:58,258 --> 00:01:00,393
As long as you have
the president's cooperation,

19
00:01:00,960 --> 00:01:02,295
I can…

20
00:01:03,396 --> 00:01:06,299
confidently hand over…

21
00:01:06,366 --> 00:01:08,902
the chairmanship.

22
00:01:10,603 --> 00:01:12,439
When I was a student here,

23
00:01:13,106 --> 00:01:17,310
Meishin was a school everyone admired.

24
00:01:17,377 --> 00:01:21,414
I will restore the prestige
of Meishin's elite brand.

25
00:01:22,248 --> 00:01:24,050
Therefore…

26
00:01:24,117 --> 00:01:27,654
I ask for your continued support,
President Kobayakawa.

27
00:01:33,860 --> 00:01:35,628
Wow…

28
00:01:35,695 --> 00:01:39,599
For someone as unmotivated as you,
Hayashi-sensei, you did your best…

29
00:01:39,666 --> 00:01:41,701
Was it Urumi-sensei's influence?

30
00:01:44,170 --> 00:01:45,905
Why don't you take a break?

31
00:01:46,673 --> 00:01:48,942
We'll handle the rest from here.

32
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:56,049
Now…

33
00:01:56,116 --> 00:02:01,154
regarding the future of the 11 students
suspected of smoking,

34
00:02:01,221 --> 00:02:04,224
-Shinjo will explain.
-Yes.

35
00:02:05,959 --> 00:02:07,393
You guys are so loud!

36
00:02:09,395 --> 00:02:10,663
Huh? What…

37
00:02:10,730 --> 00:02:12,532
Sorry! Sorry…

38
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,468
Don't get so worked up.

39
00:02:15,535 --> 00:02:17,604
We might get expelled…

40
00:02:17,670 --> 00:02:19,472
That's because you lied about not smoking.

41
00:02:23,476 --> 00:02:27,080
Still, getting expelled
for smoking just once is harsh.

42
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:30,216
Mai's mom is talking to the school today.

43
00:02:31,851 --> 00:02:35,088
-Yes.
-Let's trust Mai's mom, right?

44
00:02:42,495 --> 00:02:43,596
Urumi-sensei.

45
00:02:43,663 --> 00:02:45,532
The vice principal is back…

46
00:02:47,934 --> 00:02:51,471
So you've already won over the PTA board?

47
00:02:51,538 --> 00:02:52,672
Won over?

48
00:02:53,606 --> 00:02:55,208
Please call it prior consultation.

49
00:02:55,275 --> 00:02:58,645
Securing consensus
before a major decision.

50
00:02:58,711 --> 00:03:01,514
That's essential in business.

51
00:03:02,282 --> 00:03:06,119
There are some
who keep interfering with my plans…

52
00:03:07,287 --> 00:03:08,688
This is risk management.

53
00:03:09,522 --> 00:03:12,325
Can you stop using complicated loanwords?

54
00:03:12,392 --> 00:03:13,359
I can't follow it!

55
00:03:13,426 --> 00:03:15,295
They're not that difficult.

56
00:03:15,361 --> 00:03:17,096
-They are!
-No, they're not.

57
00:03:17,163 --> 00:03:18,865
-Principal…
-But people

58
00:03:18,932 --> 00:03:21,434
who flaunt
their Katakana English like that

59
00:03:21,501 --> 00:03:23,469
are usually the ones
who lack self-confidence

60
00:03:23,536 --> 00:03:27,040
and want to look more important
than they are.

61
00:03:28,074 --> 00:03:29,275
She has got a point.

62
00:03:29,342 --> 00:03:30,710
TOTAL INTEGRITY

63
00:03:30,777 --> 00:03:33,379
-Never heard that before.
-Right?

64
00:03:34,047 --> 00:03:35,615
I just made it up.

65
00:03:36,683 --> 00:03:38,318
From experience,

66
00:03:38,384 --> 00:03:40,653
I've met a lot of people like that.

67
00:03:41,688 --> 00:03:46,025
And you didn't do all this
because of "risk management", did you?

68
00:03:46,092 --> 00:03:49,562
You just wanted to shut Urumi-sensei
and the rest of us down, right?

69
00:03:52,498 --> 00:03:54,968
I think so too.

70
00:03:55,535 --> 00:03:56,803
This whole plan…

71
00:03:56,869 --> 00:04:00,106
Moriguchi-sensei deliberately leaked it
to Ms. Kyoko.

72
00:04:00,740 --> 00:04:04,377
So we'd take action to stop it.

73
00:04:04,944 --> 00:04:07,013
Then he could crush us

74
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:08,982
and cause maximum damage.

75
00:04:09,749 --> 00:04:13,353
It was retaliation
for me foiling his plans.

76
00:04:15,688 --> 00:04:16,923
What a jerk.

77
00:04:17,724 --> 00:04:19,025
So annoying.

78
00:04:21,928 --> 00:04:25,331
Does it matter what I think of you?

79
00:04:27,734 --> 00:04:29,836
All I know is,

80
00:04:29,902 --> 00:04:33,172
I don't lose to fools who act

81
00:04:34,073 --> 00:04:35,174
without a plan.

82
00:04:38,244 --> 00:04:39,946
Right, Vice Principal?

83
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:47,253
Out of the 11 photographed students,
six will be expelled.

84
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:50,390
The remaining five will stay.
The board has already decided.

85
00:04:51,124 --> 00:04:53,760
The PTA board gave their approval too.

86
00:04:53,826 --> 00:04:56,462
This can't be overturned.

87
00:05:02,502 --> 00:05:03,936
So in the end,

88
00:05:04,737 --> 00:05:08,241
nothing I did meant anything?

89
00:05:08,975 --> 00:05:10,843
That's not true…

90
00:05:10,910 --> 00:05:13,212
Though in this situation,
I can't say that.

91
00:05:13,279 --> 00:05:14,547
That's not true!

92
00:05:14,614 --> 00:05:15,748
Oh, he said it.

93
00:05:15,815 --> 00:05:18,851
How can you say that
when things turned out like this?

94
00:05:21,621 --> 00:05:24,123
He isn't logical at all.

95
00:05:24,924 --> 00:05:27,260
How does she even date this guy?

96
00:05:28,394 --> 00:05:30,963
But I guess it doesn't matter right now…

97
00:05:31,597 --> 00:05:34,033
Whether or not it meant anything

98
00:05:34,734 --> 00:05:36,269
depends on what you do from here.

99
00:05:41,341 --> 00:05:44,811
Their expulsion hasn't been finalized yet.

100
00:05:44,877 --> 00:05:46,145
-But…
-No buts.

101
00:05:46,713 --> 00:05:49,148
"The biggest difference
between success and failure

102
00:05:49,215 --> 00:05:52,885
is whether you give up."
Steve Jobs said so.

103
00:05:52,952 --> 00:05:54,854
Shuzo Matsuoka said,

104
00:05:54,921 --> 00:05:56,489
"Don't give up on not giving up."

105
00:05:56,556 --> 00:05:59,792
Coach Anzai said,
"If you give up, the game is over."

106
00:05:59,859 --> 00:06:02,195
All profound words,
said by profound people!

107
00:06:02,895 --> 00:06:05,765
Who's Coach Anzai?

108
00:06:05,832 --> 00:06:08,601
-From Slam Dunk-
-You can give up if you want.

109
00:06:08,668 --> 00:06:11,537
But you've already been marked
as being on the principal's side.

110
00:06:11,604 --> 00:06:13,139
If we do anything,

111
00:06:13,206 --> 00:06:16,642
they'll assume you're involved,
even if you didn't do anything.

112
00:06:16,709 --> 00:06:19,612
-You might as well help us.
-I got it!

113
00:06:20,246 --> 00:06:21,147
I got it already.

114
00:06:22,548 --> 00:06:25,184
I don't want to let it end like this.

115
00:06:25,251 --> 00:06:27,920
I'm not giving up either, Principal!

116
00:06:28,988 --> 00:06:31,858
It'd be frustrating
to walk away like this.

117
00:06:31,924 --> 00:06:35,228
I don't lose to fools who act

118
00:06:36,229 --> 00:06:37,330
without a plan.

119
00:06:37,397 --> 00:06:40,166
Who are you calling a fool? That jerk…

120
00:06:40,233 --> 00:06:42,969
So, what exactly should we do?

121
00:06:43,035 --> 00:06:45,071
That's the problem…

122
00:06:46,005 --> 00:06:48,141
If we act carelessly,

123
00:06:48,674 --> 00:06:51,043
Moriguchi-sensei will strike again.

124
00:06:51,911 --> 00:06:55,081
I'm already working on something,
so wait a little longer.

125
00:07:02,188 --> 00:07:03,956
What?

126
00:07:04,023 --> 00:07:06,793
-It's okay.
-Yes.

127
00:07:06,859 --> 00:07:08,594
Here.

128
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:12,198
TOTAL INTEGRITY

129
00:07:12,265 --> 00:07:15,468
We understand you were forced

130
00:07:15,535 --> 00:07:18,771
to smoke by Matsumoto and Iwai.

131
00:07:18,838 --> 00:07:22,675
But why did you lie and say
you didn't smoke?

132
00:07:23,776 --> 00:07:25,111
Why?

133
00:07:28,281 --> 00:07:31,651
You panicked and lied, didn't you?

134
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:35,221
It happens when you're young.

135
00:07:36,355 --> 00:07:39,392
We've heard you are a very
honest and serious student.

136
00:07:41,060 --> 00:07:43,296
She really is a good girl.

137
00:07:44,063 --> 00:07:46,165
Do you truly understand

138
00:07:46,232 --> 00:07:48,334
the gravity of what you did?

139
00:07:49,469 --> 00:07:50,470
Mai?

140
00:07:54,907 --> 00:07:55,741
Yes.

141
00:07:56,609 --> 00:07:57,944
I'm sorry.

142
00:07:58,010 --> 00:08:01,747
Do you truly understand
the gravity of what you did?

143
00:08:02,381 --> 00:08:04,217
I'm sorry.

144
00:08:04,283 --> 00:08:07,119
Do you truly understand
the gravity of what you did?

145
00:08:07,954 --> 00:08:09,055
I'm sorry.

146
00:08:10,823 --> 00:08:13,159
Three days of house suspension?
Not normal suspension?

147
00:08:13,226 --> 00:08:15,228
I'm not really sure,
but I think it's different.

148
00:08:15,294 --> 00:08:18,531
Suspension goes on your school record.

149
00:08:18,598 --> 00:08:20,566
House suspension doesn't.

150
00:08:20,633 --> 00:08:22,668
It's just considered an absence,

151
00:08:22,735 --> 00:08:24,504
so it won't affect
university applications.

152
00:08:24,570 --> 00:08:26,539
-So it's lighter than suspension?
-Yes.

153
00:08:26,606 --> 00:08:29,141
Wow, you're really knowledgeable.

154
00:08:29,208 --> 00:08:31,143
I got a house suspension

155
00:08:31,210 --> 00:08:33,779
in junior high.

156
00:08:33,846 --> 00:08:36,782
Still, I'm glad
it wasn't as bad as I thought.

157
00:08:36,849 --> 00:08:39,485
-Right?
-I'm glad.

158
00:08:39,552 --> 00:08:41,754
Voluntary withdrawal?

159
00:08:42,722 --> 00:08:43,823
Yes.

160
00:08:43,890 --> 00:08:46,592
Smoking alone is already a problem.

161
00:08:46,659 --> 00:08:49,428
But Iroha also lied.

162
00:08:50,696 --> 00:08:52,565
Lying…

163
00:08:52,632 --> 00:08:54,667
just to save yourself

164
00:08:54,734 --> 00:08:56,536
is a selfish mindset.

165
00:08:58,170 --> 00:08:59,305
We can't expect

166
00:08:59,872 --> 00:09:02,408
someone like that to repent and improve.

167
00:09:03,042 --> 00:09:04,076
-How about…
-Sounds good!

168
00:09:04,143 --> 00:09:05,645
-Well then…
-What should we do?

169
00:09:05,711 --> 00:09:08,814
It's gotta be karaoke. We'll go there,

170
00:09:08,881 --> 00:09:10,483
-get those large French fries…
-Yes!

171
00:09:18,791 --> 00:09:20,092
Sensei…

172
00:09:23,462 --> 00:09:25,898
Hina-chan and the others
only got a house suspension…

173
00:09:28,134 --> 00:09:31,237
but I'm being told to quit the school.

174
00:09:35,641 --> 00:09:38,511
Why did it end up like this?

175
00:09:45,084 --> 00:09:46,252
I'm sorry.

176
00:09:47,219 --> 00:09:50,556
Even if I apologize,
it won't make her feel better.

177
00:09:52,158 --> 00:09:54,026
I don't think it's your fault.

178
00:09:55,661 --> 00:09:59,265
First Miyazawa-kun, then Kaito-kun…

179
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:04,070
It just feels like something's
not right at this school.

180
00:10:05,938 --> 00:10:07,506
If anything…

181
00:10:08,808 --> 00:10:12,311
you seem like the only one
trying to protect us.

182
00:10:14,113 --> 00:10:16,716
She really sees what's going on…

183
00:10:23,789 --> 00:10:25,224
But still,

184
00:10:26,959 --> 00:10:28,728
I don't want to be expelled.

185
00:10:32,365 --> 00:10:33,633
I don't know what to do.

186
00:10:36,969 --> 00:10:38,738
What did your parents say?

187
00:10:40,973 --> 00:10:43,542
Don't embarrass me.

188
00:10:43,609 --> 00:10:47,046
You were the one who smoked.
You brought this on yourself.

189
00:10:47,113 --> 00:10:49,148
You're in your second year of high school.

190
00:10:49,215 --> 00:10:52,084
You're not a child anymore.
Take responsibility.

191
00:10:54,987 --> 00:10:57,456
They don't care about me.

192
00:10:58,491 --> 00:11:00,459
Emotionally negligent parents…

193
00:11:00,526 --> 00:11:01,861
NEGLIGENT PARENTS

194
00:11:01,927 --> 00:11:03,362
WHAT ARE NEGLIGENT PARENTS?

195
00:11:03,429 --> 00:11:04,263
CHARACTERISTICS OF NEGLIGENT PARENTS?

196
00:11:04,330 --> 00:11:05,164
SHOW NO INTEREST IN THEIR UPBRINGING
FAILING TO GIVE LOVE

197
00:11:05,231 --> 00:11:06,799
They provide basic needs,

198
00:11:06,866 --> 00:11:10,036
but show no interest
in the child's upbringing

199
00:11:10,102 --> 00:11:12,872
and fail to give the affection
their child deserves.

200
00:11:15,474 --> 00:11:18,344
I don't want to quit school.

201
00:11:19,912 --> 00:11:22,548
You're the only one I can rely on.

202
00:11:23,983 --> 00:11:25,685
Please help me.

203
00:11:37,229 --> 00:11:38,297
Sensei…

204
00:11:40,733 --> 00:11:45,438
Please don't tell Hina-chan and the others
about my expulsion.

205
00:11:46,572 --> 00:11:47,573
Why not?

206
00:11:48,140 --> 00:11:50,676
Everyone's happy
they only got a house suspension.

207
00:11:51,577 --> 00:11:53,946
If they find out I'm being expelled,

208
00:11:54,013 --> 00:11:55,781
they'll feel bad.

209
00:11:56,882 --> 00:11:59,318
Effects of emotionally negligent parents.

210
00:11:59,885 --> 00:12:04,323
Fear of rejection
leads to excessive people-pleasing.

211
00:12:05,725 --> 00:12:06,859
Okay.

212
00:12:07,893 --> 00:12:09,061
I won't tell anyone.

213
00:12:12,965 --> 00:12:14,467
Sensei.

214
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,836
Is it true Iroha is being expelled?

215
00:12:16,902 --> 00:12:19,238
It got out immediately.

216
00:12:19,305 --> 00:12:21,006
Why is she the only one getting expelled

217
00:12:21,073 --> 00:12:22,842
when we only got a house suspension?

218
00:12:22,908 --> 00:12:24,877
Even if you ask me…

219
00:12:25,711 --> 00:12:28,047
I mean…

220
00:12:28,114 --> 00:12:29,482
I don't really know…

221
00:12:29,548 --> 00:12:31,283
How can you not know?

222
00:12:32,618 --> 00:12:34,520
I don't really understand…

223
00:12:34,587 --> 00:12:37,056
-Just answer me clearly!
-Stop it.

224
00:12:39,058 --> 00:12:40,359
Yelling at her won't help!

225
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:42,695
-Are you on her side?
-It's not like

226
00:12:43,429 --> 00:12:46,232
she wants Iroha expelled.

227
00:12:46,298 --> 00:12:48,200
You saw how she was with me and Miyazawa.

228
00:12:51,570 --> 00:12:53,672
Isn't this all your fault?

229
00:12:53,739 --> 00:12:54,607
What?

230
00:12:54,673 --> 00:12:57,476
Didn't you get Mai's mom to help you

231
00:12:57,543 --> 00:12:59,845
and throw Iroha under the bus?

232
00:12:59,912 --> 00:13:02,715
-Hey.
-What are you talking about?

233
00:13:02,782 --> 00:13:04,583
You guys were bullying Iroha!

234
00:13:06,318 --> 00:13:08,187
Then you got lectured by the teacher

235
00:13:08,254 --> 00:13:10,523
and had to stop.
That pissed you off, right?

236
00:13:11,290 --> 00:13:13,926
So you tried to get her
kicked out of school.

237
00:13:13,993 --> 00:13:16,395
Like you should talk.
You stole my boyfriend.

238
00:13:16,462 --> 00:13:18,798
Still going on about that? Gross.

239
00:13:19,698 --> 00:13:22,134
-What?
-That's enough!

240
00:13:25,538 --> 00:13:27,406
Hina-chan wouldn't do anything like that.

241
00:13:30,943 --> 00:13:32,611
Then why are you only getting expelled?

242
00:13:36,849 --> 00:13:39,852
What should I have done?

243
00:13:39,919 --> 00:13:43,489
You told me not to act carelessly,

244
00:13:43,556 --> 00:13:45,591
but if we don't do something fast,

245
00:13:45,658 --> 00:13:48,761
Naito will be expelled.

246
00:13:50,462 --> 00:13:53,065
The classroom atmosphere
is already terrible.

247
00:13:53,132 --> 00:13:55,835
I honestly can't take it anymore.

248
00:13:57,536 --> 00:14:00,239
How long are we supposed to wait?

249
00:14:01,574 --> 00:14:03,209
At this rate,

250
00:14:03,275 --> 00:14:06,679
we'll face more expulsion incidents.

251
00:14:06,745 --> 00:14:09,682
And we won't be able to stop them all.

252
00:14:09,748 --> 00:14:10,950
That's why we need

253
00:14:11,016 --> 00:14:13,085
a fundamental solution.

254
00:14:13,919 --> 00:14:14,753
What?

255
00:14:17,323 --> 00:14:20,593
Moriguchi-sensei's plan

256
00:14:20,659 --> 00:14:23,329
to expel 75 students.

257
00:14:24,163 --> 00:14:25,397
I want to stop it.

258
00:14:26,332 --> 00:14:28,267
He says

259
00:14:28,334 --> 00:14:30,803
it's for reviving Meishin

260
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:35,007
and ensuring business stability.

261
00:14:35,074 --> 00:14:38,410
But I think there's more to it.

262
00:14:38,477 --> 00:14:41,747
Something darker…Something twisted.

263
00:14:42,781 --> 00:14:44,316
If we can figure out the reason,

264
00:14:44,950 --> 00:14:48,220
maybe we can convince him
to abandon the plan.

265
00:14:50,322 --> 00:14:53,125
That's what I'm trying to uncover.

266
00:14:55,294 --> 00:14:58,264
There's a new gym by the station.

267
00:14:58,330 --> 00:15:00,299
Apparently,

268
00:15:00,366 --> 00:15:03,002
you ride a bike to the music in the dark.

269
00:15:03,869 --> 00:15:07,139
My waistline's been bothering me lately.

270
00:15:07,206 --> 00:15:10,709
